00:17:53.839 --> 00:17:56.839
But now, we go to the Scottish Borders with artist

00:17:56.839 --> 00:18:02.680
Adebanji Alade to visit one of the UK's most amazing places.

00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:04.799
And joining him is someone you know whose art is as bright

00:18:06.279 --> 00:18:07.319
This place looks amazing.

00:18:07.319 --> 00:18:10.119
And I am not here just by luck.

00:18:10.119 --> 00:18:11.799
This place was chosen by someone

00:18:11.799 --> 00:18:14.279
whose funny ways

00:18:14.279 --> 00:18:22.240
made lots of kids laugh for years.

00:18:25.359 --> 00:18:27.200
Mallet's Mallett is a word game.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:29.720
You must not stop. You must not wait.

00:18:29.720 --> 00:18:31.599
Or you get hit on the head like this.

00:18:31.599 --> 00:18:32.680
Or like this.

00:18:32.680 --> 00:18:34.799
Timmy Mallett asked me to meet him here

00:18:34.799 --> 00:18:36.720
at the bottom of the great Leaderfoot Viaduct

00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:38.880
in the Scottish Borders. Because now he is more likely

00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:41.759
to hold a paintbrush than his famous big foam mallet.

00:18:41.759 --> 00:18:43.960
Here he comes. Oh, wow.

00:18:43.960 --> 00:18:45.759
Adebanji!

00:18:45.759 --> 00:18:47.359
Timmy! It is great to meet you.

00:18:47.359 --> 00:18:50.960
Tell me, why are we here?

00:18:50.960 --> 00:18:53.359
When I am not being funny with Mallett's mallet,

00:18:53.359 --> 00:18:56.319
I am The Cycling Artist. And I ride my bike everywhere.

00:18:56.319 --> 00:18:59.799
And I paint pictures everywhere I go.

00:18:59.799 --> 00:19:03.640
Now I understand, because this place looks great.

00:19:03.640 --> 00:19:06.039
We are setting up our stands so I can paint him

00:19:06.039 --> 00:19:11.400
while he paints a picture of the view.

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:15.160
The south of Scotland is a secret beautiful place.

00:19:15.160 --> 00:19:19.799
People often drive past quickly on their way to the Highlands. Really,

00:19:19.799 --> 00:19:24.160
they are missing out because this place has so much to see.

00:19:24.160 --> 00:19:29.000
This bridge was an old train line that ran for 80 years.

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:30.920
The last Indiana Jones movie was filmed here.

00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.480
Wow.

00:19:33.480 --> 00:19:41.440
It is a great place and it brings all kinds of people,

00:19:44.400 --> 00:19:47.640
including great artists like Adebaji.

00:19:47.640 --> 00:19:49.920
Jokes aside, Timmy's setup is quite strange.

00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:54.680
Timmy, I have never seen a painting stand on a bike.

00:19:54.680 --> 00:20:00.359
I wanted to find a way to paint on the bike.

00:20:00.359 --> 00:20:06.000
So I figured out how to attach the stand to the bike.

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.920
I painted the bike myself with water paints.

00:20:07.920 --> 00:20:11.119
It is part of who I am.

00:20:11.119 --> 00:20:14.720
In 1984, Timmy joined the kids' TV show Wide Awake Club.

00:20:14.720 --> 00:20:18.599
Later he hosted Wacaday, which was on until 1992.

00:20:18.599 --> 00:20:21.240
What do you think of the shorts? Do you like them?

00:20:21.240 --> 00:20:23.640
His face and sayings were known by a whole group of people.

00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:24.839
Hit my head like this.

00:20:24.839 --> 00:20:25.880
Or like this.

00:20:25.880 --> 00:20:28.519
Really great.

00:20:28.519 --> 00:20:30.680
But more recently, art has become his full-time job.

00:20:30.680 --> 00:20:34.960
Timmy, have you always been an artist?

00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:42.920
Oh, yes. Art has been very important in our family.

00:20:42.920 --> 00:20:45.759
My dad was an artist. He would say, "Look closely."

00:20:45.759 --> 00:20:46.799
Look closely at things. Let the light and dark parts

00:20:46.799 --> 00:20:49.759
make the picture.

00:20:49.759 --> 00:20:53.119
And my mum was always a great judge.

00:20:53.119 --> 00:21:01.079
Oh!

00:21:01.480 --> 00:21:04.319
"Mum, what do you think of my painting?"

00:21:04.319 --> 00:21:09.720
She would say...

00:21:09.720 --> 00:21:11.359
"Very nice, dear. I like the frame better."

00:21:11.359 --> 00:21:12.799
In 2018, Timmy went on

00:21:12.799 --> 00:21:14.720
a 2500-mile painting and biking trip around Europe.

00:21:14.720 --> 00:21:16.160
It is a long way to Santiago!

00:21:16.160 --> 00:21:17.799
His brother Martin gave him the idea.

00:21:17.799 --> 00:21:18.839
Martin had Down's Syndrome.

00:21:18.839 --> 00:21:22.559
He died just before Timmy left.

00:21:22.559 --> 00:21:26.480
Martin was not stopped by his problems with talking and learning.

00:21:26.480 --> 00:21:34.440
He was never held back by Down's Syndrome.

00:21:35.480 --> 00:21:37.400
He would say, "You and me, I'm happy."

00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:39.319
That means enjoy the moment right now.

00:21:39.319 --> 00:21:41.960
It is easy to enjoy the moment on the bike.

00:21:41.960 --> 00:21:44.759
Dear Martin shows me that,

00:21:44.759 --> 00:21:47.079
give it a try,

00:21:47.079 --> 00:21:50.240
try your best to do as much as you can.

00:21:50.240 --> 00:21:51.680
See if you can. Every day.

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:55.000
Wonderful. What a great attitude.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:57.000
And you know what, Adebanji? I'm finished.

00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:59.079
All right, I will come and see yours first.

00:21:59.079 --> 00:22:01.720
Oh, wow. I love it.

00:22:01.720 --> 00:22:03.799
The difference in the light hitting these posts.

00:22:03.799 --> 00:22:05.960
You have these dark shapes against the sky,

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:07.640
and then, boom, the light comes out.

00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:09.039
Wonderful. Brilliant.

00:22:09.039 --> 00:22:11.480
Thanks.

00:22:11.480 --> 00:22:13.160
Brilliant.

00:22:13.160 --> 00:22:14.839
Shall we look at yours?

00:22:14.839 --> 00:22:16.519
OK. Right.

00:22:16.519 --> 00:22:17.799
I know that guy.

00:22:17.799 --> 00:22:19.880
Yeah.

00:22:19.880 --> 00:22:21.880
There is some colour in this, right?

00:22:21.880 --> 00:22:28.359
Yeah.

00:22:28.440 --> 00:22:35.160
It shows what you do, how you do it, and what you use. Thank

00:22:35.160 --> 00:22:43.119
you, that is really, really great. Thank you.

00:22:44.519 --> 00:22:51.039
great. Thank you. Both paintings are so lovely. I used to love

00:22:51.039 --> 00:22:55.160
watching Timmy Mallett.

00:22:55.160 --> 00:22:57.079
Time to say hello to our next guests.

00:22:57.079 --> 00:23:02.599
They are two actors who are also related.

00:23:02.599 --> 00:23:08.920
It's Dame Imelda Staunton and her daughter Bessie Carter.

00:23:09.000 --> 00:23:14.039
I am with famous actors, because you just won

00:23:14.039 --> 00:23:20.680
your fifth Olivier Award! Amazing! How do you feel? Greedy! Still

00:23:20.680 --> 00:23:27.480
greedy. It is very nice, yes. You will not get much more from

00:23:27.480 --> 00:23:37.400
me on that. You two are now mother and daughter on stage

00:23:38.559 --> 00:23:40.440
in Mrs Warren's Profession. It is set in

00:23:40.440 --> 00:23:44.079
old times. When it was first written, it is about the difficult relationship

00:23:44.079 --> 00:23:49.039
between them. Then a secret comes out

00:23:49.039 --> 00:23:56.079
that changes things.

00:23:56.160 --> 00:24:00.200
Yes, it is about a mother and daughter who have

00:24:00.200 --> 00:24:02.920
been apart and have not known each other because of how things

00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:08.200
were. We meet them over a few days when they have a kind

00:24:08.200 --> 00:24:10.599
of argument that neither of them wants but

00:24:10.599 --> 00:24:19.680
they must have. And to have a play written in 1893, about

00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:24.119
the problems of women at work or at home or just in

00:24:24.119 --> 00:24:28.240
life, that women again are not treated the same. George Bernard

00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:33.039
Shaw strongly supported women. This play was banned because

00:24:33.039 --> 00:24:36.359
they did not want to know. It was partly banned because of the name.

00:24:36.359 --> 00:24:48.720
A woman having a title was not allowed. Not cool then.

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:53.119
Now, you act with your mum, Bessie. This is your first time

00:24:53.119 --> 00:25:00.799
acting with her. How does it feel? Terrible, awful! We are both

00:25:00.799 --> 00:25:08.000
having a terrible time!

00:25:08.079 --> 00:25:10.359
It is really great. It is a real treat. We are

00:25:10.359 --> 00:25:17.079
having a lovely time. It feels strangely normal to us.

00:25:17.079 --> 00:25:22.680
We are just two actors in a room trying to tell a story.

00:25:22.680 --> 00:25:28.880
So it is a real treat. And the packed lunches are really good. That

00:25:28.880 --> 00:25:35.359
is all we talk about! You have the hard-boiled eggs for the 11 o'clock

00:25:35.359 --> 00:25:45.079
break, and then we compare food. Living the dream! And your dad is an

00:25:45.079 --> 00:25:48.720
actor. You have directed him before. Is it good working with family,

00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:54.599
or not so much? When you get to that place where you are on the

00:25:54.599 --> 00:25:57.680
floor, working together, the relationship, the father and son

00:25:57.680 --> 00:26:03.680
with my father, you trust each other. I will give him a suggestion, and

00:26:03.680 --> 00:26:09.400
he would say OK and get up and do it. But it was a great thing for him

00:26:09.400 --> 00:26:13.440
to let me direct. It is a great short film, and he is wonderful in it. I

00:26:13.440 --> 00:26:17.799
am really glad I did that. I have something real

00:26:17.799 --> 00:26:21.200
with my father that I can look at and show his

00:26:21.200 --> 00:26:25.440
grandchildren later on. It was a great experience. Really

00:26:25.440 --> 00:26:31.279
special, isn't it? And you said you had not acted together

00:26:31.279 --> 00:26:34.279
before, but then we found this photo. We wondered what was

00:26:34.279 --> 00:26:45.680
going on. This was a performance of Mamma Mia!!. It was last week!

00:26:45.680 --> 00:26:50.839
Started young.

00:26:51.400 --> 00:26:53.279
Started young.

00:26:53.279 --> 00:26:59.119
